{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9f1a859a-9fa5-4db8-bf9a-941ff7e76f81","content":"**`ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"`** — ✅ Yes, this is correct. It's the iOS platform-specific that adjusts page padding to respect the safe area (notch, Dynamic Island, home indicator). You'll need the namespace:\n\n```xml\nxmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n```\n\n**`IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` on Grid** — ❌ This is **not** a real .NET MAUI API. The tutorial is likely outdated or incorrect. There's no `IgnoreSafeArea` property on layouts.\n\n### Background image behind safe area\n\nTo have a background image extend edge-to-edge while keeping content in the safe area, layer them in a Grid:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n             ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"False\">\n    <Grid>\n        <!-- Background fills entire screen -->\n        <Image Source=\"bg.png\" Aspect=\"AspectFill\" />\n\n        <!-- Content respects safe area via padding -->\n        <Grid Padding=\"{OnPlatform iOS='44,0,34,0'}\">\n            <!-- your content here -->\n        </Grid>\n    </Grid>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nSet `UseSafeArea=\"False\"` so the background extends fully, then manually apply safe-area-like padding to your content layer. You can also use `On<iOS>().SetUseSafeArea(...)` in code-behind and read `SafeAreaInsets` for dynamic values instead of hardcoding.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2b98b646-2faf-4d9e-874c-fb1dbac65f89","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI safe area handling on iOS, specifically about two properties:\n\n1. `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` - a platform-specific property for ContentPage\n2. `IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` - a property on Grid for background images\n\nLet me check what I know about these APIs in .NET MAUI, particularly for .NET 10.\n\nIn .NET MAUI, the iOS safe area handling is done via platform-specifics. The correct API is:\n\n- `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` - This is the iOS platform-specific for pages. The namespace would be `xmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"`.\n\n\n- `IgnoreSafeArea` doesn't actually exist in .NET MAUI as a property on layouts like Grid. That was a Xamarin.Forms concept. In .NET MAUI, safe area handling works differently through the platform-specific approach on pages rather than individual layout controls.\n\nFor extending a background image behind the safe area while keeping content within bounds, the typical pattern would be layering an `AbsoluteLayout` with a background that fills the entire screen, while using `UseSafeArea` on the page itself to constrain the content appropriately. So `UseSafeArea=\"True\"` is the correct approach for .NET MAUI on .NET 10, but `IgnoreSafeArea` isn't actually a real property—that tutorial might be outdated or inaccurate. I should clarify this distinction for the user.","outputTokens":1280,"requestId":"0453:343824:13516AB:15B2D7A:6A027D1D"},"id":"5c66626e-96bd-451a-b9a9-ca213a93d757","timestamp":"2026-05-12T01:07:02.295Z","parentId":"6ecd3fe7-9d4c-4d04-8835-f671371259e8"}
